Popular Yoruba actor, Gbolagade Akinpelu, popularly known as Ogun Majek, is dead. It was gathered that the actor died on Thursday morning at his Imalefalafia, Oke-Ado, Ibadan home. Nollywood actor and producer, Tunde Ola-Yusuf, confirmed his death in a post on his Facebook page. The post reads, “From him we come and onto him we shall return. Alh. Gbolagade Akinpelu Ogunmajek has returned to his creator. “May God almighty rest his soul among the righteous.” READ ALSO Ekiti Assembly mourns ex-lawmaker, Ayodele He, however did not disclose the cause of his death. The actor was reported to have battled a prolonged illness before his death.